name: Pioneers of African-American Cinema
description: This newly preserved collection features more than 20 films made by groundbreaking African American directors for black audiences from 1915 to 1946.

name: Pioneers: First Women Filmmakers*
description: This collection restores films from women who tackled hot-button issues, transcended norms, and left a mark on the history of cinema and the industry.

name: The Twilight Zone (Original Series)
description: Hosted by creator Rod Serling, this groundbreaking anthology series presents tales of the supernatural that are often tinged with social commentary.

name: Monty Python's Flying Circus
description: The Monty Python players make their mark with a winning mix of wit, ingenuity and brilliant timing -- and a penchant for mockery and cross-dressing.

name: Star Trek
description: Led by unflappable Capt. Kirk, the crew of the starship Enterprise delves deep into the far reaches of space to explore new worlds and civilizations.

name: Bamse
description: Bamse is the sweetest brown bear around -- and he's also the strongest bear in the world when he eats a special type of honey his grandma makes.

name: Star Trek: The Animated Series
description: The starship Enterprise takes on new adventures in this colorful cartoon series featuring the voices of the original 'Star Trek' cast.

name: Fawlty Towers
description: Haughty Basil Fawlty and his bossy wife try to raise the profile of their Fawlty Towers Hotel, but endless mix-ups arise, leading to farcical lunacy.

name: Panda! Go Panda!
description: When little Mimiko is left home alone while her grandmother is away on a trip, a panda father and his young son decide to move in.

name: Porridge
description: A crafty career criminal and his clueless cellmate serve time subverting authority and attempting to stay out of trouble in this prison sitcom.

name: Dad's Army
description: This beloved sitcom follows the unlikely heroes of the volunteer British Home Guard as they prepare for German invasion in World War II.

name: Barbapapa
description: A compassionate family of adorable creatures can take any form. They travel the world helping people and animals wherever they go.

name: The Perrine Story
description: Alone, Perrine travels to France to find her grandfather. Because he disowned her parents, she avoids him and becomes a worker in his factory.

name: Once Upon a Time... Man
description: Tag along on a journey of discovery as a family travels from caves to pyramids to modern cities in this classic animated series about human history.

name: Conan, The Boy in Future
description: In the 21st century, a devastating war has left only scattered islands of survivors, but a young boy and his sweetheart represent hope for the future.
